22:27','Our goal as  Ticket Rush  is to make your purchasing experience easy, efficient and equitable, so we can get you on your way to live events as quickly as possible. The following purchase policies are designed to ensure your satisfaction and understanding of the purchase process on tktrush.com This Purchase Policy establishes a part of our Usage Conditions. We hereby state that you will be deemed as read, understood and agreed the provisions of the Purchase Policy fully by being a member with our website and/or purchasing a ticket; and please visit our FAQ page before any purchase in the event of that you have any request or complain pursuant to the provisions of this Purchase Policy.\r\n\r\nSALES POLICY\r\n1. As an authorized ticket agent, Ticket Rush sells tickets on behalf of the venue, promoter or producer that produces the event for which you buy a ticket. We refer to the venue, promoter, or producer from whom we obtain tickets to sell to you as our \"Event Partner\". Tickets purchased from Ticket Rush are subject to a per ticket service charge and a non-refundable per order handling charge. Ticket Rush does not set ticket prices or determine seating plans. The person who purchases a ticket hereby declares and undertakes that this ticket remains the property of the Event Partner and is a personal revocable license, which may be withdrawn and admission refused at any time upon refunding the printed purchase price. A ticket shall not be used for advertising, promotions, contests or sweepstakes, unless the Event Provider gives formal written permission. Unlawful resale (or attempted unlawful resale) of a ticket is grounds for seizure or cancellation of that ticket without refund or other compensation.\r\n\r\n2. You can only purchase tickets from Ticket Rush within the ticket purchase limit predefined for the event. This ticket purchase limit is defined in the first page of purchase. It is aimed through this application to prevent the unfair ticket purchases. Tickets may be restricted to a maximum number per person, per credit card and, for some events; a restriction may apply per household. We reserve the right to cancel tickets without prior notice purchased in excess of this number. Ticket Rush accept payments online using Visa and MasterCard credit/debit card in AED (United Arab Emirates Dirhams) , being UAE as Ticket Rush country of domicile. If Credit Card Online is selected as the payment method, the details on the customers ID (Card holders ID) should exactly match that of the credit card used to make the purchase.\r\n\r\n3. The tickets are generally sold through various sales channels including the Internet, Call Center, Ticket Rush Retail Outlets. As all the sales channels are using the same ticketing system and inventory therefore popular events tickets may be sold out quickly. Occasionally, additional tickets may be available prior to the event, however Ticket Rush does not control this inventory or its availability.\r\n\r\n4. If you select courier delivery option for your tickets, it is required that you will be at the delivery address on the date of the delivery and you need to present an official proof of your identification and the credit card that you used for the payment for the ticket(s). For security purposes the courier may not deliver the tickets any person other than the credit card holder. The courier charge has been collected from your credit card during the purchase; therefore you should not make any payment to the courier. In the case of indicating an address outside the delivery areas of courier services, it is not possible to deliver the tickets. Delivery information such as Customers Name, Location Address and Contact Number will be stored for delivery purposes only. Other personal identifiable information will not be stored.\r\n\r\n5. It is your responsibility to control and protect your tickets. Please store your tickets in a secure place once you will obtain them. Please note that direct sunlight or heat can sometimes damage tickets.\r\n\r\n6. Occasionally, events are cancelled or postponed by the promoter, team, performer or venue for a variety of reasons. If the event is cancelled, refund procedures will be announced by the Event Partner. If the event was moved or rescheduled, the venue or promoter may set refund limitations. It is your responsibility to ascertain whether an event has been cancelled and the date and time of any events. If an event is cancelled or rescheduled, we will use reasonable endeavors to notify ticket holders of the cancellation once we have received the relevant authorization from the Event Partner. We do not guarantee that ticket holders will be informed of such cancellation before the date of the event.\r\n\r\n7. As a general rule, all ticket sales are final and non-refundable. Policies set forth by Event Partners, prohibit us from issuing exchanges or refunds after a purchase has been made or for lost, stolen, damaged or destroyed tickets. Tickets cannot be exchanged or refunded after purchase unless the performance is cancelled. If the ticket holder is unable to attend the rescheduled event a full refund will be offered. Full refunds for tickets purchased prior to the date of the original event will be given up to the face value of the tickets purchased plus the relevant per ticket service charge. All the refunds of any transactions amount against any purchase through this website would be refunded to the original mode of payment.\r\nIf the event was moved or rescheduled, the venue or Event Partners may set refund limitations. Additionally, Event Partners have right to alter or vary the program due to events or circumstances beyond its reasonable control without being obliged to refund monies or exchange tickets. It is the customers responsibility to comply with the latest refund date and other instructions as defined by the Event Partners. In this sense Ticket Rush has no liability whatsoever for such transactions. In order to make refund for the cancelled or postponed events, the tickets should be physically delivered to the Ticket Rush Retail Outlets. Please click for further information on the cancelled or changed events.\r\n\r\n8. This ticket is issued subject to the Rules and Regulations of the venue and Event Partner. Breach of any of these Rules and Regulations or any unacceptable behavior likely to cause damage, nuisance or injury shall entitle the venue or Event Partner to eject you from the venue. The venue reserves the right to refuse admission should patrons breach any Rules and Regulations of the venue or Event Partner. The venue may on occasions have to conduct security searches to ensure the safety of the patrons.\r\n\r\n9. The exit and entries from/to the venue shall be conducted pursuant to the rules and regulations of the Event Partner and the venue. It is a common understanding that there will be no pass-outs or re-admissions of any kind. Every effort to admit latecomers will be made at a suitable break in the event, but admission cannot always be guaranteed by Ticket Rush\r\n\r\n10. The unauthorized use of photographic and recording equipment is prohibited by terms and conditions set by Event Partners. Tapes or films may be destroyed. Laser pens, mobile phones, may also be prohibited.\r\n\r\n11.The Event Partners are entitled to prohibit the entrance of pets or animals (except for guide dogs).\r\n\r\n12. The Event Partners may also prohibit patrons to bring food and drink from outside.\r\n\r\n13. The venue, Event Partner and Ticket Rush accept no responsibility for any personal property.\r\n\r\n14. The ticket holder has a right only to a seat of a value corresponding to that stated on the ticket and the venue or Event Partner reserves the right to provide alternative seats to those specified on the ticket.\r\n\r\n15. Ticket Rush has no liability or responsibility as to the tickets, ticket sales and/or the events excluding the price on the ticket and the service charge related to the ticket. The customers hereby agree, declare and undertake that the liability of Ticket Rush is limited under this article and they shall not hold Ticket Rush liable for any incidents excluding the liability expressly defined hereunder.\r\n\r\n16. Please note that you will be required to give the reference number of your purchase if you shall require any information from Ticket Rush related to your ticket purchase. Therefore, please note and keep this reference number.\r\n\r\n17. All of these terms and conditions are governed by UAE Law.','TICKET RUSH SALES POLICIES','','publish','closed','closed','','ticket-rush-sales-policies','','','2017-04-27 18:22:27','2017-04-27 18:22:27','',0,'http://www.tktrush.com/tkt2/?page_id=52',0,'page','',0),(53,1,'2017-04-27 18:22:27','2017-04-27 18:22:27','Our goal as  Ticket Rush  is to make your purchasing experience easy, efficient and equitable, so we can get you on your way to live events as quickly as possible. The following purchase policies are designed to ensure your satisfaction and understanding of the purchase process on tktrush.com This Purchase Policy establishes a part of our Usage Conditions. We hereby state that you will be deemed as read, understood and agreed the provisions of the Purchase Policy fully by being a member with our website and/or purchasing a ticket; and please visit our FAQ page before any purchase in the event of that you have any request or complain pursuant to the provisions of this Purchase Policy.\r\n\r\nSALES POLICY\r\n1. As an authorized ticket agent, Ticket Rush sells tickets on behalf of the venue, promoter or producer that produces the event for which you buy a ticket. We refer to the venue, promoter, or producer from whom we obtain tickets to sell to you as our \"Event Partner\". Tickets purchased from Ticket Rush are subject to a per ticket service charge and a non-refundable per order handling charge. Ticket Rush does not set ticket prices or determine seating p